Nge2}) 11... Nbd7 12. O-O Ba6 13. Rb3 Qa5 {This position has been seen many
times in practice. Overall, Black should be slightly better thanks to his
better coordinated pieces and better structure. For example:} 14. Bxa6 Qxa6 15.
Re1 Rfd8 $1 $146 {[%csl Gc4,Gd5][%cal Ge7e6,Gd7b6] with a plan to attack
White's light squared weaknesses.} *

